"In this Georgic, he shows us what station is most proper for the bees, and when they begin to gather honey: how tu call thein home when they swarm; and how to part them when they are engaged in battle. From hence he takes occasion to discover their different kinds; and, after an escarsion, relates their pradent and politic adminisiration of affairs, and the general diseases that often rage in their hives, with the proper symptoms and remedics of each disease. In the last place he lays down a method of repairing their kind, sup- posing their whole oreed lost ; and gives at large the history of iis invention."